                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/10379: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-03T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 3, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Your No. 111, April 26, 4 p.m., last sentence. The Department does not
                    consider it desirable to comply with Hugessen’s suggestion since he is in
                    communication with his Government and it would be inappropriate for the
                    Department to initiate discussions involving primarily Anglo-Turkish
                    relations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
